Catalogue
of the Lepidoptera of Belgium
Cossidae
Tortricidae
Choreutidae

Tortricidae occur worldwide and are most diverse in temperate and tropical regions. About 5000 species have been described, many of them are of economic importance (Scoble 1992: 255).
Identification: Benander 1950, Bentinck & Diakonoff 1968, Bradley 1959, Bradley & Martin 1956, Bradley, Tremewan & Smith 1973, 1979, Danilewski & Kuznetzov 1968, 1990, van Deurs 1956, Diakonoff 1962, Diakonoff & Dorst 1982, Hannemann 1961, 1964, Janmoulle 1959, Kennel 1908-1921, Kostjuk 1980, Kuznetzov 1989b, Larsen & Vilhelmsen 1986-1990, Obraztsov 1953a, b, 1954-1957, 1958-1968, 1961-1967, Opheim 1964, 1967, 1968, 1970, Razowski 1959, 1963, 1969, 1970, 1981, 1983, 1984, 1987, 1991, 2001, 2002.
Nomenclature according to Fauna Europea.
Species in Belgium: 377.
